      "title": "react",
      "description": "<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 16px; line-height: 1.65; letter-spacing: 0.1px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;\">Key features:</p><ul style=\"padding-left: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">pretty small (~9kb, ~4kb gzipped)</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">fast</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">simple to configure</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">simple to extend</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">support automatic LTR and RTL text direction switching for Arabic languages</li></ul><p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 16px; line-height: 1.65; letter-spacing: 0.1px; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;\">Of course, it's not so powerful as other complex editors. It DOES NOT:</p><ul style=\"padding-left: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">‚úó change HTML generated by a browser (sometimes it can be dirty)</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">‚úó sanitize HTML (you can use&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/sanitize-html\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(203, 56, 55); text-decoration: none; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.4;\">sanitize-html</a>)</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">‚úó contain advanced features as others (like table editor, image editor and so on)</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 1em;\">‚úó support old browsers (I